              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Occasionally yes — strong topical authority from related content, perfect intent alignment, and SERP features (like featured snippets) can overcome KD predictions. Ahrefs data shows 31% of top-10 pages for high-KD keywords have fewer backlinks than the score suggests necessary. But KD 60+ almost always requires a meaningful backlink profile.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Is KD 0 worth targeting?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Often yes. KD 0 keywords are typically very specific long-tail queries with little or no competitive content. Even low search volume (50–200/month) adds up across many such terms, and they often convert better than head terms because they match specific intent.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Does keyword difficulty change over time?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
